# Runtime local-state EKF profile override.
#
# wheel_spin_imu is the field default after the 2026-07-14 receive-time split.
# Ranger wheel x/y/yaw remains the long-term pose anchor outside SPINNING. In
# SPINNING=2, the EKF input preprocessor removes the wheel feedback's early yaw
# integration and follows corrected JT128 IMU yaw-rate through physical settle.
# Shadow +180/-180 tests ended within 0.031deg of IMU with zero XY drift and no
# IMU fallback, integration gap, or forced settle.
# wheel_imu is the immediate rollback profile.
# wheel_only remains the rollback/isolation profile.
# The twist_imu_vyaw_only profile was rejected as a runtime default because
# unbounded IMU yaw integration required a 1.023m/13.38deg truth correction.
# wheel_pose_imu_vyaw remains available for controlled diagnostics: Ranger
# /wheel/odom is normalized to /wheel/odom_ekf and anchors x/y/yaw pose plus
# forward vx, while corrected /lidar_imu_bias_corrected contributes the only
# yaw-rate measurement.
# twist_imu_vyaw_only remains available only for controlled diagnostics that
# explicitly observe EKF yaw-rate reset behavior; do not use it as a navigation
# default.
# wheel_imu_primary_vyaw passed static and short-spin gates but failed the
# repeated two-point field gate on 2026-07-10: local yaw separated from wheel by
# about 44.2 degrees and the goal degraded to 35.6cm / 13.2deg. Keep it only for
# bounded diagnostics until the dynamic IMU divergence is explained.
# wheel_pose_imu_vyaw, wheel_imu_pose_soft_yaw_015,
# wheel_imu_twist_soft_yaw_012, wheel_imu_twist_soft_yaw_010,
# wheel_imu_twist_soft_yaw_015, wheel_imu_yaw_offset_m061,
# wheel_imu_xy_shear_p062, wheel_imu_xy_lateral_m061,
# wheel_imu_xy_lateral_m040,
# wheel_imu_xy_lateral_m050,
# wheel_imu_xy_lateral_m085,
# wheel_imu_xy_lateral_m120,
# wheel_imu_xy_lateral_soft_yaw_016,
# wheel_imu_xy_lateral_yaw_p979_n1011,
# wheel_imu_soft_yaw_018,
# wheel_imu_soft_yaw_016,
# wheel_imu_soft_yaw_015, wheel_imu_soft_yaw_014, wheel_imu_soft_yaw_010, wheel_imu_soft_yaw,
# wheel_xy_imu_vyaw, wheel_xy_imu_yaw, wheel_xy_diff_yaw_imu,
# twist_imu and twist_wheel_yaw_imu remain available for controlled experiments.
# wheel_pose_imu_vyaw keeps wheel x/y/yaw pose and wheel vx, but removes
# wheel yaw-rate so corrected IMU gyro is the only EKF yaw-rate input.
# wheel_imu_pose_soft_yaw_015 raises only wheel yaw pose covariance while
# leaving wheel yaw-rate at the stable default. wheel_imu_twist_soft_yaw_012
# keeps wheel yaw pose at the stable default while raising wheel yaw-rate
# covariance to 0.12 after the 0.15 candidate reduced yaw error but still
# exceeded the two-point truth gate. wheel_imu_twist_soft_yaw_010 is the
# smallest yaw-rate-only step above the stable 0.08 default.
# wheel_imu_twist_soft_yaw_015 keeps wheel yaw pose at the stable default while raising wheel yaw-rate covariance to
# 0.15. wheel_imu_yaw_offset_m061 keeps the stable EKF fields but rotates the
# preprocessed wheel odom plane by -0.061 rad for controlled calibration.
# wheel_imu_xy_shear_p062 keeps the stable EKF fields but applies a +0.062
# y-to-x shear to anchored wheel odom position for controlled calibration.
# wheel_imu_xy_lateral_m061 keeps the stable EKF fields but applies a -0.061
# x-to-y body-lateral shear to anchored wheel odom position for controlled
# calibration.
# wheel_imu_xy_lateral_m040 keeps the stable EKF fields and applies a smaller
# -0.040 x-to-y body-lateral shear for controlled A/B tests.
# wheel_imu_xy_lateral_m050 keeps the stable EKF fields and applies an
# interpolated -0.050 x-to-y body-lateral shear for controlled A/B tests.
# wheel_imu_xy_lateral_m085 keeps the stable EKF fields and applies a midpoint
# -0.085 x-to-y body-lateral shear for controlled A/B tests.
# wheel_imu_xy_lateral_m120 keeps the stable EKF fields and applies a stronger
# -0.120 x-to-y body-lateral shear for controlled A/B tests.
# wheel_imu_xy_lateral_soft_yaw_016 combines that -0.061 body-lateral shear
# with the 0.16 wheel yaw/yaw-rate covariance floors for controlled A/B tests.
# wheel_imu_xy_lateral_yaw_p979_n1011 keeps the same lateral shear and adds
# sign-specific yaw scaling: positive yaw 0.979, negative yaw 1.011.
# wheel_imu_soft_yaw_018 raises both wheel yaw and yaw-rate
# covariance floors to 0.18. wheel_imu_soft_yaw_016 raises both floors to
# 0.16 after the 0.15 candidate nearly passed the two-point gate but still
# exceeded the true relocalization threshold. wheel_imu_soft_yaw_015 raises both floors to
# 0.15, wheel_imu_soft_yaw_014 raises both floors to 0.14, and
# wheel_imu_soft_yaw_010 is the smallest soft-yaw step above the stable 0.08 default.
# wheel_imu_soft_yaw is the more aggressive 0.25
# variant. wheel_xy_imu_vyaw keeps wheel x/y pose and vx but lets corrected IMU
# gyro be the only yaw-rate input. wheel_xy_imu_yaw keeps wheel x/y pose and
# wheel+IMU yaw-rate but drops wheel yaw pose. twist_imu intentionally does not
# fuse chassis-integrated wheel pose. wheel_xy_diff_yaw_imu keeps wheel yaw pose
# and wheel twist, but fuses wheel x/y only as differential motion.
# twist_imu_vyaw_only is stricter: it uses
# wheel forward speed but corrected IMU gyro is the only yaw-rate input.
# twist_wheel_yaw_imu also drops wheel x/y pose, but keeps the wheel yaw pose
# anchor while propagating x/y from wheel forward speed.
export NJRH_LOCAL_STATE_EKF_PROFILE="${NJRH_LOCAL_STATE_EKF_PROFILE:-wheel_spin_imu}"
